                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d469">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">853.79681/89: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Consul General at Algiers</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Wiley</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-05-13T22:00:00-04:00"
                            >May 13, 1943—10 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>924. For Murphy. Your 735, April 28, midnight and Lisbon’s 975 of May 3, 4 p.m.
                    to the Department, repeated to you. The whole question of utilizing the Azores
                    as you suggest has been under consideration by the Department and by our Mission
                    in Portugal for some time past. No definite solution has been reached although
                    the matter is being pressed. You will be advised as soon as the Department <pb
                        facs="0541" n="529" xml:id="pg_529"/> has a reply to an urgent telegram
                    which is being sent to Portugal.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
